df['Month_Year'] = df['date'].dt.to_period("M")

# Create a pivot table
pivot_table = pd.pivot_table(df, values='transaction_amount', index='Month_Year', columns='item_name')

# Plotting using Matplotlib
pivot_table.plot(kind='bar', y=df['item_name'].unique(), figsize=(12, 8), title='Revenue by Item Name')
plt.xlabel('Month-Year')
plt.ylabel('Transaction Amount')
plt.legend(title='Item Name', bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc='upper left')  # Adjust legend position
plt.show()

Report

**We can observe from the above analysis that the primary issue is that most sales in 2022 occurred in the month of December. The highest-selling item during that month was the Sandwich, followed by Frankie in the second position. Other items experienced lower sales compared to other months. A similar trend is observed in January 2023, with sales gradually decreasing in the subsequent months.**

Customer preferences indicate a higher inclination towards Cold Coffee, Sugarcane Juice, and Pani Puri. This trend is evident when visualizing the data, which shows that fast food items are more popular and have higher sales compared to beverages.

Evaluating the impact of payment methods on revenue, it is observed that the most effective method for generating higher revenue is using cash rather than online payments.

Investigating the performance of staff members based on gender, it is evident that males exhibit a slightly higher performance in sales compared to females, although the difference is not significant.

Exploring the popularity of items at different times of the day, we find that during the night and morning hours, people prefer visiting restaurants. During both of these times, sandwiches and frankies are the more popular items compared to other times of the day.
